あるがまま = あるがまま = arugamama = as things are, accepting reality as it is.
人生をあるがままに生きる。 = じんせいを あるがままに いきる = jinsei o arugamama ni ikiru = Live life as it is.
一期一会 = いちごいちえ = ichigo ichie = once-in-a-lifetime encounter - Cherishing each moment as unique.
一期一会の出会いを大切に。 = いちごいちえの であいを たいせつに = ichigo ichie no deai o taisetsu ni = Treasure every once-in-a-lifetime meeting.
はんこ = はんこ = hanko = hanko stamp, personal seal - Japanese name stamp used instead of signature.
書類にはんこを押した。 = しょるいにはんこを おした = shorui ni hanko o oshita = I stamped the document with my hanko.
会釈 = えしゃく = eshaku = light greeting bow (15°) - Casual bow for acquaintances.
軽く会釈して挨拶した。 = かるく えしゃくして あいさつした = karuku eshaku shite aisatsu shita = I greeted him with a light bow.
敬礼 = けいれい = keirei = respectful bow (30-40°) - Business or formal bow toward superiors.
上司に敬礼した。 = じょうしに けいれいした = jōshi ni keirei shita = I bowed respectfully to my boss.
最敬礼 = さいけいれい = saikeirei = deepest reverent bow (45°+) - For high respect or formal occasions.
社長に最敬礼をした。 = しゃちょうに さいけいれいをした = shachō ni saikeirei o shita = I gave the deepest bow to the president.
土下座 = どげざ = dogeza = dogeza (kneeling bow with forehead to ground) - Extreme bow for deep apology.
土下座して謝った。 = どげざして あやまった = dogeza shite ayamatta = I apologized on my knees with my forehead to the ground.
お宝 = おたから = otakara = treasure, valuable possession, cherished item - Often used casually for precious things.
このゲームでお宝を見つけた！ = このゲームで おたからを みつけた！ = kono gēmu de otakara o mitsuketa! = I found treasure in this game!
財宝 = ざいほう = zaihō = treasure, wealth - Valuable objects or riches.
海賊が財宝を隠した。 = かいぞくが ざいほうを かくした = kaizoku ga zaihō o kakushita = The pirates hid the treasure.
まさか = まさか = masaka = no way, impossible, you can't be serious - Expresses disbelief.
まさか本当なのか？ = まさか ほんとうなのか？ = masaka hontō na no ka? = No way, is that true?
歳月 = さいげつ = saigetsu = years, passage of time - The flow of years/time.
歳月が人を変える。 = さいげつが ひとを かえる = saigetsu ga hito o kaeru = Time changes people.
ずいぶん = ずいぶん = zuibun = very, quite, considerably, surprisingly - Indicates degree or surprise.
ずいぶん寒くなったね。 = ずいぶん さむくなったね = zuibun samuku natta ne = It’s gotten quite cold, hasn’t it?
とりあえず = とりあえず = toriaezu = for now, tentatively, first of all - Temporary measure.
とりあえずこれでいいよ。 = とりあえず これで いいよ = toriaezu kore de ii yo = This will do for now.
つまり = つまり = tsumari = in other words, basically - Used to summarize or clarify.
つまり君の言うことは間違ってるよ。 = つまり きみの いうことは まちがってるよ = tsumari kimi no iu koto wa machigatteru yo = In other words, you’re wrong.
つもり = つもり = tsumori = intention, plan, purpose - What one intends to do.
留学するつもりだ。 = りゅうがくする つもりだ = ryūgaku suru tsumori da = I intend to study abroad.
素晴らしい = すばらしい = subarashī = wonderful, amazing, excellent, superb - Strong admiration.
この景色は素晴らしい！ = このけしきは すばらしい！ = kono keshiki wa subarashī! = This view is amazing!
約束 = やくそく = yakusoku = promise, appointment, agreement - Casual promise or formal arrangement.
約束を守るのが大事だ。 = やくそくを まもるのが だいじだ = yakusoku o mamoru no ga daiji da = Keeping promises is important.
済まない = すまない = sumanai = I'm sorry (informal), excuse me - Casual apology with regret.
本当に済まない。 = ほんとうに すまない = hontō ni sumanai = I’m really sorry.
安心する = あんしんする = anshin suru = to feel relieved, to be at ease.
安心して大丈夫だよ。 = あんしんして だいじょうぶだよ = anshin shite daijōbu da yo = Don’t worry, it’s okay.
さすが = さすが = sasuga = as expected, impressive as usual - Compliment for living up to reputation.
さすがプロだね。 = さすが プロだね = sasuga puro da ne = As expected from a pro.
無理 = むり = muri = impossible, unreasonable, excessive - Beyond one’s power or “no way”.
それは無理だと思う。 = それは むりだ とおもう = sore wa muri da to omou = I think that’s impossible.
気づかない = きづかない = kizukanai = to not notice, to be unaware.
彼は自分の間違いに気づかない。 = かれは じぶんの まちがいに きづかない = kare wa jibun no machigai ni kizukanai = He doesn’t notice his own mistake.
暗黒 = あんこく = ankoku = darkness (evil/sinister), dark age - Negative or evil darkness.
暗黒の時代が続いた。 = あんこくの じだいが つづいた = ankoku no jidai ga tsuzuita = A dark age continued.
生き延びる = いきのびる = ikinobiru = to survive, to live on - Continue existing through danger.
厳しい状況でも生き延びた。 = きびしい じょうきょうでも いきのびた = kibishii jōkyō demo ikinobita = He survived even in harsh conditions.
真実 = しんじつ = shinjitsu = truth, sincerity - Facing or speaking the truth.
真実を話してくれ。 = しんじつを はなしてくれ = shinjitsu o hanashite kure = Tell me the truth.
実際 = じっさい = jissai = reality, actuality, in practice - Real-life situation.
実際にはそんなに簡単じゃない。 = じっさいには そんなに かんたんじゃない = jissai ni wa sonna ni kantan ja nai = In reality, it’s not that simple.
無効化 = むこうか = mukōka = disabling, invalidation, override - Making something no longer valid.
システムを無効化する。 = システムを むこうかする = shisutemu o mukōka suru = Disable the system.
はずだ = はずだ = hazu da = is supposed to be, expected to be - Strong logical expectation.
彼はもう着いているはずだ。 = かれは もう ついているはずだ = kare wa mō tsuite iru hazu da = He should have arrived by now.
ふざける = ふざける = fuzakeru = to play around, to kid, to mess around - "fuzakeruna" = stop kidding.
ふざけるなよ！ = ふざけるなよ！ = fuzakeruna yo! = Stop kidding around!
確かに = たしかに = tashikani = definitely, surely, certainly - Strong agreement or realization.
確かにその通りだ。 = たしかに そのとおりだ = tashikani sono tōri da = That’s definitely true.
現在 = げんざい = genzai = now, current, present time - The present moment.
現在は何時ですか？ = げんざいは なんじですか？ = genzai wa nanji desu ka? = What time is it now?
手伝う = てつだう = tetsudau = to help, to lend a hand with work - Collaborative help.
荷物を持つ手伝いをします。 = にもつを もつ てつだいを します = nimotsu o motsu tetsudai o shimasu = I’ll help carry the luggage.
助ける = たすける = tasukeru = to help, to rescue, to save - Help in crisis or danger.
危ない！助けて！ = あぶない！ たすけて！ = abunai! tasukete! = Watch out! Help!
瓦解 = がかい = gakai = collapse, crumbling (of a system) - System or group falling apart.
組織が瓦解した。 = そしきが がかいした = soshiki ga gakai shita = The organization collapsed.
売国奴 = ばいこくど = baikokudo = traitor to one’s country - Strong term for national betrayer.
彼を売国奴と呼んだ。 = かれを ばいこくどと よんだ = kare o baikokudo to yonda = They called him a traitor to the country.
忘却 = ぼうきゃく = bōkyaku = forgetfulness, oblivion - Deliberately putting something out of mind.
過去を忘却する。 = かこを ぼうきゃくする = kako o bōkyaku suru = Forget the past completely.
監獄 = かんごく = kangoku = prison, jail - Formal term for prison.
監獄に入れられた。 = かんごくに いれられた = kangoku ni irerareta = He was put in prison.
裸の王様 = はだかのおうさま = hadaka no ōsama = the naked king / Emperor’s New Clothes - Situation where people pretend to see what isn’t there.
それは裸の王様だ。 = それは はだかのおうさまだ = sore wa hadaka no ōsama da = That’s just the Emperor’s New Clothes situation.
狼狽売り = ろうばいうり = rōbaiuri = panic selling - Selling in panic (stock market).
株価下落で狼狽売りが起きた。 = かぶかげらくで ろうばいうりが おきた = kabuka geraku de rōbaiuri ga okita = Panic selling occurred due to the stock drop.
組み立て = くみたて = kumitate = assembly, putting together - Building or assembling parts.
家具の組み立てを手伝う。 = かぐの くみたてを てつだう = kagu no kumitate o tetsudau = Help with assembling the furniture.
効率 = こうりつ = kōritsu = efficiency - Doing things with minimal waste.
効率を上げる方法を考えよう。 = こうりつを あげる ほうほうを かんがえよう = kōritsu o ageru hōhō o kangaeyō = Let’s think of ways to improve efficiency.
起死回生 = きしかいせい = kishikaisei = dramatic comeback, resuscitation - Revival from a desperate situation.
起死回生の一手が必要だ。 = きしかいせいの いってが ひつようだ = kishikaisei no itte ga hitsuyō da = We need a dramatic comeback move.
漁夫の利 = ぎょふのり = gyofu no ri = fisherman’s profit - Gaining benefit while others fight.
漁夫の利を得た。 = ぎょふのりを えた = gyofu no ri o eta = He gained the fisherman’s profit.
二兎を追う者は一兎をも得ず = にうをおうものはいつをもえず = nito o ou mono wa itto mo ezu = he who chases two rabbits catches neither.
二兎を追う者は一兎をも得ずという proverb だ。 = にうをおうものはいつをもえずという proverb だ = nito o ou mono wa itto mo ezu to iu proverb da = It’s the proverb “he who chases two rabbits catches neither.”
千里眼 = せんりがん = senrigan = far-sighted vision, clairvoyance - Ability to see far ahead.
彼は千里眼を持っているようだ。 = かれは せんりがんを もっているようだ = kare wa senrigan o motte iru yō da = He seems to have far-sighted vision.
油断大敵 = ゆだんたいてき = yudan taiteki = negligence is a great enemy.
油断大敵だから気をつけろ。 = ゆだんたいてきだから きをつけろ = yudan taiteki dakara ki o tsukero = Negligence is a great enemy, so be careful.
一石二鳥 = いっせきにちょう = isseki nichō = one stone two birds - Achieving two things with one action.
この方法は一石二鳥だ。 = このほうほうは いっせきにちょうだ = kono hōhō wa isseki nichō da = This method kills two birds with one stone.
見つける = みつける = mitsukeru = to find, to discover - Action of locating something hidden.
みんなを見つけます。 = みんなを みつけます = minna o mitsukemasu = I will find everyone.
豪華 = ごうか = gōka = luxurious, splendid, extravagant, gorgeous - Visually impressive and opulent.
豪華なパーティーだった。 = ごうかな パーティーだった = gōka na pātī datta = It was a luxurious party.
凝っている = こっている = koutte iru = elaborate, intricate, sophisticated - High-effort refined design.
この時計のデザインは凝っている。 = このとけいの デザインは こっている = kono tokei no dezain wa koutte iru = This watch has a very elaborate design.
救急車 = きゅうきゅうしゃ = kyūkyūsha = ambulance - Emergency medical transport vehicle.
救急車を呼んで！ = きゅうきゅうしゃを よんで！ = kyūkyūsha o yonde! = Call an ambulance!
救急隊 = きゅうきゅうたい = kyūkyūtai = ambulance crew, emergency medical team - The personnel on the ambulance.
救急隊が到着した。 = きゅうきゅうたいが とうちゃくした = kyūkyūtai ga tōchaku shita = The ambulance crew has arrived.
救急医療 = きゅうきゅういりょう = kyūkyū iryō = emergency medicine, emergency care - Urgent medical services.
この病院は救急医療が充実している。 = このびょういんは きゅうきゅういりょうが じゅうじつしている = kono byōin wa kyūkyū iryō ga jūjitsu shite iru = This hospital has excellent emergency medical care.
一生懸命 = いっしょうけんめい = isshōkenmei = with all one’s might, wholeheartedly - Full effort and concentration.
一生懸命頑張ります。 = いっしょうけんめい がんばります = isshōkenmei ganbarimasu = I will do my very best.
拷問 = ごうもん = gōmon = torture - Inflicting severe pain for punishment or information.
拷問に耐えられなかった。 = ごうもんに たえられなかった = gōmon ni taerarenakatta = He couldn’t endure the torture.
虐待 = ぎゃくたい = gyakutai = abuse, mistreatment - Ongoing physical or emotional abuse.
動物虐待は許されない。 = どうぶつぎゃくたいは ゆるされない = dōbutsu gyakutai wa yurusarenai = Animal abuse is unacceptable.
処刑 = しょけい = shokei = execution (capital punishment) - Legal killing as punishment.
死刑が執行され処刑された。 = しけいが しっこうされ しょけいされた = shikei ga shikkō sare shokei sareta = He was executed after the death sentence.
誇り = ほこり = hokori = pride, honor, dignity - Positive self-worth from achievements.
自分の仕事に誇りを持っている。 = じぶんの しごとに ほこりを もっている = jibun no shigoto ni hokori o motte iru = I take pride in my work.
5歳児に説明するように = ごさいじ に せつめい する ように = gosaiji ni setsumei suru yō ni = explain it like I’m a 5-year-old.
5歳児に説明するように教えて。 = ごさいじに せつめいするように おしえて = gosaiji ni setsumei suru yō ni oshiete = Explain it to me like I’m five years old.
盗んだ = ぬすんだ = nusunda = stole (past tense) - Took without permission.
財布を盗んだ犯人が捕まった。 = さいふを ぬすんだ はんにんが つかまった = saifu o nusunda hannin ga tsukamatta = The person who stole the wallet was caught.
奪った = うばった = ubatta = snatched, took by force - Violent or sudden seizure.
自由を奪った。 = じゆうを うばった = jiyū o ubatta = They took away our freedom.
略奪した = りゃくだつ した = ryōdatsu shita = plundered, looted - Large-scale organized theft.
村を略奪した。 = むらを りゃくだつした = mura o ryōdatsu shita = They plundered the village.
上半身 = じょうはんしん = jōhanshin = upper body - Part of the body above the waist.
上半身を鍛えている。 = じょうはんしんを きたえている = jōhanshin o kitaete iru = I am training my upper body.
暗黙 = あんもく = anmoku = implicit, tacit, unspoken, unsaid - Something understood or agreed upon without being directly expressed in words (unspoken rules or understandings).
彼は暗黙のうちに同意した。 = かれは あんもくの うちに どういした = kare wa anmoku no uchi ni dōi shita = He agreed implicitly / tacitly.
ただ…ってだけなのに = ただ…ってだけなのに = tada... tte dake nanoni = It's just... but still; Even though it's just...; Only... but yet - Expresses frustration or surprise that something big happens despite a simple/minor thing.
ただ挨拶しただけなのに、無視された。 = ただ あいさつしただけなのに、むしされた = tada aisatsu shita dake nanoni, mushi sareta = I only greeted him, but I got ignored.
ズバ抜けてる = ずばぬけてる = zubanuketeru = outstanding, exceptional, superb, head and shoulders above the rest - Remarkably better or more impressive than average; stands out sharply.
彼の才能はズバ抜けてる。 = かれの さいのうは ずばぬけてる = kare no sainō wa zubanuketeru = His talent is outstanding.
しかも = しかも = shikamo = moreover, furthermore, what's more, on top of that - Adds emphatic or surprising additional information that amplifies the previous statement.
値段が高い。しかも品質が悪い。 = ねだんが たかい。しかも ひんしつが わるい = nedan ga takai. shikamo hinshitsu ga warui = The price is high. What's more, the quality is bad.
キモい = きもい = kimoi = gross, disgusting, creepy, revolting - Strong informal slang for something that feels repulsive or creepy (stronger and more casual than 気持ち悪い).
その虫、キモい！ = そのむし、きもい！ = sono mushi, kimoi! = That bug is gross/creepy!
気持ち悪い = きもちわるい = kimochi warui = unpleasant, disgusting, gross, nauseating, creepy - More standard/polite way to express something feels bad or repulsive.
この絵、ちょっと気持ち悪い。 = このえ、ちょっと きもちわるい = kono e, chotto kimochi warui = This painting is a bit creepy/unpleasant.
ゾッとする = ぞっとする = zotto suru = to shudder, to feel a chill, to be horrified - Physical reaction of shuddering from something creepy, scary, or grotesque.
その話を聞いてゾッとした。 = そのはなしを きいて ぞっとした = sono hanashi o kiite zotto shita = Hearing that story gave me chills / made me shudder.
意味わかんない = いみわかんない = imi wakan nai = I don't get it, it makes no sense, I don't understand - Very casual way to express confusion or that something is illogical.
意味わかんないんだけど。 = いみわかんないんだけど = imi wakan nai n dakedo = I seriously don't get it.
いらってくる = いらってくる = ira tte kuru = to get irritated, to start feeling annoyed/frustrated - The feeling of irritation gradually building up.
だんだんいらってくる。 = だんだん いらってくる = dandan ira tte kuru = I'm starting to get irritated.
～に近い = ～にちかい = ~ ni chikai = close to ~, similar to ~, near to ~, bordering on ~ - Indicates proximity or similarity in quality/state.
彼の考えは私の考えに近い。 = かれの かんがえは わたしの かんがえに ちかい = kare no kangae wa watashi no kangae ni chikai = His thinking is close to mine.
謎 = なぞ = nazo = mystery, riddle, enigma, puzzle - Something unexplained, perplexing, or difficult to solve.
この事件はまだ謎が多い。 = このじけんはまだ なぞがおおい = kono jiken wa mada nazo ga ōi = There are still many mysteries surrounding this case.
結局 = けっきょく = kekkyoku = after all, in the end, ultimately, eventually - Indicates the final outcome or conclusion, often after much thought or time.
色々考えたけど、結局行かないことにした。 = いろいろ かんがえたけど、けっきょく いかないことにした = iroiro kangaeta kedo, kekkyoku ikanai koto ni shita = I thought about it a lot, but in the end I decided not to go.
イケてる = いけてる = iketeru = cool, awesome, hot, trendy, attractive - Slang for someone or something stylish, good-looking, or impressive.
あの人、すごくイケてるね！ = あのひと、すごく いけてるね！ = ano hito, sugoku iketeru ne! = That person is super cool / attractive!
～のように = ～のように = ~ no yō ni = like ~, as if ~, in the manner of ~ - Used for comparisons or describing manner.
彼は子供のように泣いた。 = かれは こどものように ないた = kare wa kodomo no yō ni naita = He cried like a child.
ため口 = ためぐち = tameguchi = casual speech, informal speech, familiar language - Relaxed speech used with friends or equals (opposite of polite speech).
友達と話す時はため口でいいよ。 = ともだちとはなすときは ためぐちで いいよ = tomodachi to hanasu toki wa tameguchi de ii yo = When talking with friends, casual speech is fine.
せめて = せめて = semete = at least, at the very least - Expresses the minimum acceptable or desired action/situation.
プレゼントは買えないけど、せめてメッセージを送りたい。 = ぷれぜんとは かえないけど、せめて めっせーじをおくりたい = purezento wa kaenai kedo, semete messēji o okuritai = I can’t buy a present, but at least I want to send a message.
効率的に = こうりつてきに = kōritsu-teki ni = efficiently, productively - Doing something with minimal waste of time, energy, or resources.
仕事を効率的に進める。 = しごとを こうりつてきに すすめる = shigoto o kōritsu-teki ni susumeru = Proceed with the work efficiently.
衝動的 = しょうどうてき = shōdō-teki = impulsive, impetuous - Acting suddenly based on emotion or urge without much thought.
彼は衝動的な買い物をしてしまう。 = かれは しょうどうてきな かいものを してしまう = kare wa shōdō-teki na kaimono o shite shimau = He has a habit of making impulsive purchases.
尺度得点 = しゃくどとくてん = shakudo tokuten = scale score - A standardized or converted score used in tests, assessments, or statistics.
このテストの尺度得点は85点だった。 = このテストの しゃくどとくてんは 85てんだった = kono tesuto no shakudo tokuten wa 85-ten datta = The scale score on this test was 85 points.
お小遣い = おこづかい = okozukai = allowance (especially pocket money given by wife to husband) - Monthly allowance, commonly used for money a wife gives her husband for personal expenses.
妻からお小遣いをもらっている。 = つまから おこづかいを もらっている = tsuma kara okozukai o moratte iru = I receive allowance from my wife.
ひどい = ひどい = hidoi = terrible, awful, severe, cruel, unfair - Strong negative judgment for something bad, mean, or harsh.
それはひどい！ = それは ひどい！ = sore wa hidoi! = That’s terrible / mean!
キモい = きもい = kimoi = gross, disgusting, creepy, revolting - Strong informal slang expressing disgust or creepiness.
その虫、キモい！ = そのむし、きもい！ = sono mushi, kimoi! = That bug is gross!
気短 = きみじか = kimijika = impatient, short-tempered - Describes someone who lacks patience and gets frustrated easily.
彼は気短だから待つのが苦手だ。 = かれは きみじかだから まつのが にがてだ = kare wa kimijika dakara matsu no ga nigate da = He’s impatient, so he’s bad at waiting.
我慢できない = がまんできない = gaman dekinai = cannot bear it, cannot stand it, I can’t wait anymore - Expresses inability to tolerate something any longer.
もう我慢できない！ = もう がまんできない！ = mō gaman dekinai! = I can’t take it anymore!
短気 = たんき = tanki = short-tempered, quick to anger, impatient - Tendency to get angry or frustrated quickly.
彼は短気だからすぐに怒る。 = かれは たんきだから すぐに おこる = kare wa tanki dakara sugu ni okoru = He’s short-tempered, so he gets angry easily.
焦る = あせる = aseru = to be impatient, to be in a hurry, to feel flustered/anxious - Feeling rushed or anxious due to time pressure.
時間がないので焦っている。 = じかんがないので あせっている = jikan ga nai node asette iru = I’m in a hurry because I don’t have much time.
犠牲 = ぎせい = gisei = sacrifice, victim - Giving up something valuable for a greater cause, or a person who suffers as a result of an event.
家族のために人生を犠牲にした。 = かぞくのために じんせいを ぎせいにした = kazoku no tame ni jinsei o gisei ni shita = He sacrificed his life for his family.
献身 = けんしん = kenshin = devotion, dedication, self-sacrifice - Strong selfless commitment or dedication to someone or something.
彼女は子供たちへの献身的な愛を示した。 = かのじょは こどもたちへの けんしんてきな あいを しめした = kanojo wa kodomo-tachi e no kenshin-teki na ai o shimeshita = She showed devoted love for her children.
犠牲にする = ぎせいにする = gisei ni suru = to sacrifice (something) - Verb form meaning to give up or forfeit something.
自分の時間を犠牲にして手伝った。 = じぶんの じかんを ぎせいにして てつだった = jibun no jikan o gisei ni shite tetsudatta = I sacrificed my own time to help.
可愛い子ぶる = かわいいこぶる = kawaii ko buru = to act cute, to play innocent/cute, to pretend to be cute - Often with a nuance of deliberate acting or exaggeration.
彼女は上司の前でいつも可愛い子ぶる。 = かのじょは じょうしのまえで いつも かわいいこぶる = kanojo wa jōshi no mae de itsumo kawaii ko buru = She always plays cute in front of her boss.
甘える = あまえる = amaeru = to act spoiled, to be pampered, to fawn on, to depend on someone’s kindness - Behaving childishly or cutely to seek indulgence or favor.
彼女は彼に甘えている。 = かのじょは かれに あまえている = kanojo wa kare ni amaete iru = She’s acting spoiled / leaning on him cutely.
猫をかぶる = ねこをかぶる = neko o kaburu = to act demure/innocent, to hide one's true nature, to put on an innocent front - Pretending to be gentle or cute while actually having a different personality (often with negative connotation).
彼女は彼の前で猫をかぶっている。 = かのじょは かれのまえで ねこをかぶっている = kanojo wa kare no mae de neko o kabutte iru = She acts all innocent and demure in front of him.
あざとい = あざとい = azatoi = cunningly cute, sly, calculating (especially when pretending to be innocent or adorable) - Deliberately acting cute in a manipulative or strategic way.
その仕草、ちょっとあざといね。 = そのしぐさ、ちょっと あざといね = sono shigusa, chotto azatoi ne = That gesture is a bit calculatingly cute / sly.
監督 = かんとく = kantoku = director (film/TV), coach, supervisor - Person in charge of directing a movie, team, or project.
その映画の監督は誰ですか？ = そのえいがの かんとくは だれですか？ = sono eiga no kantoku wa dare desu ka? = Who is the director of that movie?
演出家 = えんしゅつか = enshutsuka = stage director, production director - Director focused on artistic staging, especially in theater.
彼は舞台の演出家として有名だ。 = かれは ぶたいの えんしゅつかとして ゆうめいだ = kare wa butai no enshutsuka toshite yūmei da = He is famous as a stage director.
監督する = かんとくする = kantoku suru = to direct, to supervise - Verb form meaning to oversee or direct a project or team.
彼は新しい映画を監督する。 = かれは あたらしいえいがを かんとくする = kare wa atarashii eiga o kantoku suru = He will direct a new movie.
確かに = たしかに = tashika ni = indeed, certainly, that's true, you've got a point - Used to affirm or agree with something.
確かにその通りだ。 = たしかに そのとおりだ = tashika ni sono tōri da = That's true indeed / You've got a point.
虎 = とら = tora = tiger
虎の威を借る狐 = とらのいをかるきつね = tora no i o karu kitsune = a fox borrowing the tiger's might - A weak person acting powerful by relying on someone stronger (similar to "riding on coattails").
彼は上司の力で威張っているだけ、典型的な虎の威を借る狐だ。 = かれは じょうしのちからで いばっているだけ、てんけいてきな とらのいをかるきつねだ = kare wa jōshi no chikara de ibatte iru dake, tenkei-teki na tora no i o karu kitsune da = He's just acting arrogant using his boss's power — a classic case of a fox borrowing the tiger's might.
食うか食われるか = くうか くわれるか = kū ka kuwareru ka = eat or be eaten, survival of the fittest, dog-eat-dog - A ruthless competitive situation where you must dominate or be dominated.
この業界は食うか食われるかの世界だ。 = このぎょうかいは くうか くわれるかの せかいだ = kono gyōkai wa kū ka kuwareru ka no sekai da = This industry is a dog-eat-dog world.
弱肉強食 = じゃくにくきょうしょく = jyakuniku kyōshoku = survival of the fittest, the law of the jungle, the weak are meat and the strong eat - The strong dominate the weak.
弱肉強食の世の中だ。 = じゃくにくきょうしょくの よのなかだ = jyakuniku kyōshoku no yo no naka da = It’s a world where the strong eat the weak.
張り子の虎 = はりこのとら = hariko no tora = paper tiger - Something or someone that appears powerful but is actually weak and harmless.
彼の脅しは張り子の虎だ。 = かれのおどしは はりこのとらだ = kare no odoshi wa hariko no tora da = His threats are just a paper tiger.
口先だけ = くちさきだけ = kuchisaki dake = all talk, just lip service, empty words - Promising or talking big without real action.
彼の約束はいつも口先だけだ。 = かれのやくそくは いつも くちさきだけだ = kare no yakusoku wa itsumo kuchisaki dake da = His promises are always just empty talk.
物質 = ぶっしつ = busshitsu = matter, substance, material - Anything that has mass and occupies space; physical material.
この実験ではさまざまな物質を使います。 = このじっけんでは さまざまな ぶっしつを つかいます = kono jikken de wa samazama na busshitsu o tsukaimasu = We use various materials in this experiment.
究極 = きゅうきょく = kyūkyoku = ultimate, final, extreme, absolute - The highest or most fundamental level.
究極の目標は世界一になることだ。 = きゅうきょくのもくひょうは せかいいちに なることだ = kyūkyoku no mokuhyō wa sekai ichi ni naru koto da = My ultimate goal is to become number one in the world.
絶対 = ぜったい = zettai = absolute, definitely, never (with negative), absolutely - Expresses strong certainty or strong negation.
明日絶対行くよ！ = あした ぜったい いくよ！ = ashita zettai iku yo! = I’ll definitely go tomorrow!
水銀 = すいぎん = suigin = mercury (chemical element) - The silvery liquid metal (Hg), also known as quicksilver.
水銀は常温で液体の金属だ。 = すいぎんは じょうおんで えきたいの きんぞくだ = suigin wa jōon de ekitai no kinzoku da = Mercury is a liquid metal at room temperature.
マーキュリー = マーキュリー = mākyurī = Mercury - Used for proper names (god, planet, brand, etc.).
マーキュリーはローマ神話の神だ。 = マーキュリーは ろうましんわの かみだ = mākyurī wa rōma shinwa no kami da = Mercury is the god in Roman mythology.
雑談 = ざつだん = zatsudan = small talk, casual chat, chitchat - Informal conversation about everyday topics.
会議の前に少し雑談した。 = かいぎのまえに すこし ざつだんした = kaigi no mae ni sukoshi zatsudan shita = We had a little small talk before the meeting.
世間話 = せけんばなし = sekenbanashi = small talk, gossip about daily life - Casual talk about common affairs or everyday matters.
おばあちゃんは世間話が大好きだ。 = おばあちゃんは せけんばなしが だいすきだ = obāchan wa sekenbanashi ga daisuki da = Grandma loves small talk about daily life.
暇つぶし = ひまつぶし = himatsubushi = killing time, pastime - Doing something just to pass the time.
暇つぶしに雑談しよう。 = ひまつぶしに ざつだんしよう = himatsubushi ni zatsudan shiyō = Let’s chat to kill some time.
満足 = まんぞく = manzoku = satisfaction, contentment - Feeling of fulfillment when expectations are met.
結果に満足している。 = けっかに まんぞくしている = kekka ni manzoku shite iru = I am satisfied with the result.
納得 = なっとく = nattoku = understanding, acceptance, being convinced - Satisfaction that comes from logical understanding.
彼の説明に納得した。 = かれの せつめいに なっとくした = kare no setsumei ni nattoku shita = I was convinced by his explanation.
充実 = じゅうじつ = jūjitsu = fulfillment, richness, completeness - Deep sense of a meaningful and satisfying life/experience.
毎日が充実している。 = まいにちが じゅうじつしている = mainichi ga jūjitsu shite iru = Every day feels fulfilling.
どこにいたんだ = どこにいたんだ = doko ni itan da = Where were you? / Where have you been? - Casual way to ask someone’s whereabouts (often with slight annoyance or concern).
お前、どこにいたんだ？ = おまえ、どこにいたんだ？ = omae, doko ni itan da? = Where the hell have you been?
限定 = げんてい = gentei = limited, restricted, exclusive - Something available only in limited quantity, time, or scope.
これは数量限定商品です。 = これは すうりょうげんてい しょうひんです = kore wa sūryō gentei shōhin desu = This is a limited quantity product.
走って = はしって = hashitte = running (te-form), run! - Te-form of 走る (to run); can mean “run!” as a request/command.
早く走って！ = はやく はしって！ = hayaku hashitte! = Run quickly! / Hurry up and run!
反応時間 = はんのうじかん = hannō jikan = reaction time - The time it takes to respond to a stimulus (psychological, sports, etc.).
彼の反応時間はとても速い。 = かれの はんのうじかんは とても はやい = kare no hannō jikan wa totemo hayai = His reaction time is very fast.
応答時間 = おうとうじかん = ōtō jikan = response time - The time a system or machine takes to respond to input.
このサーバーの応答時間が遅い。 = このサーバーの おうとうじかんが おそい = kono sābā no ōtō jikan ga osoi = This server’s response time is slow.
計画 = けいかく = keikaku = plan, project, scheme - A detailed arrangement for future action.
旅行の計画を立てている。 = りょこうの けいかくを たてている = ryokō no keikaku o tatete iru = I’m making plans for the trip.
抜け穴 = ぬけあな = nukeana = loophole, escape hole - A flaw in a rule or system that allows one to bypass its intent.
法律の抜け穴を見つけた。 = ほうりつの ぬけあなを みつけた = hōritsu no nukeana o mitsuketa = I found a loophole in the law.
承知いたしました = しょうち いたしました = shōchi itashimashita = Understood; I acknowledge (humble & formal) - Polite way to confirm understanding in business settings.
ご連絡、承知いたしました。 = ごれんらく、しょうち いたしました = go-renraku, shōchi itashimashita = I have received and understood your message.
サプライヤー = サプライヤー = sapuraiyā = supplier - Loanword for a company or person that supplies goods/services.
新しいサプライヤーを探しています。 = あたらしい サプライヤーを さがしています = atarashii sapuraiyā o sagashite imasu = We are looking for a new supplier.
供給業者 = きょうきゅうぎょうしゃ = kyōkyū gyōsha = supplier, provider - More formal/native term for supplier.
この部品の供給業者はどこですか？ = このぶひんの きょうきゅうぎょうしゃは どこですか？ = kono buhin no kyōkyū gyōsha wa doko desu ka? = Who is the supplier of this part?
沈黙 = ちんもく = chinmoku = silence, quietness (often meaningful or heavy silence) - A significant or profound silence.
部屋に沈黙が流れた。 = へやに ちんもくが ながれた = heya ni chinmoku ga nagareta = Silence fell over the room.
方位磁石 = ほういじしゃく = hōi jishaku = compass (for navigation/direction) - Device used to find direction.
方位磁石を使って道を確認した。 = ほういじしゃくを つかって みちを かくにんした = hōi jishaku o tsukatte michi o kakunin shita = I checked the direction using a compass.
羅針盤 = らしんばん = rashinban = nautical compass, mariner’s compass - Traditional or nautical compass.
船長は羅針盤を見ながら航海した。 = せんちょうは らしんばんを みながら こうかいした = senchō wa rashinban o minagara kōkai shita = The captain navigated while looking at the compass.
全面 = ぜんめん = zenmen = entire surface, full-scale, comprehensive, across the board - Covering everything completely.
計画を全面的に見直す。 = けいかくを ぜんめんてきに みなおす = keikaku o zenmen-teki ni minaosu = We will review the plan comprehensively.
全体的 = ぜんたいてき = zentai-teki = overall, holistic, as a whole - Looking at the entire picture.
全体的に見て問題はない。 = ぜんたいてきに みて もんだいは ない = zentai-teki ni mite mondai wa nai = Overall, there is no problem.
倉庫 = そうこ = sōko = warehouse, storehouse, depot - Building for storing goods.
商品は倉庫に保管してあります。 = しょうひんは そうこに ほかんしてあります = shōhin wa sōko ni hokan shite arimasu = The products are stored in the warehouse.
歓迎会 = かんげいかい = kangeikai = welcome party, welcome reception - Party held to welcome newcomers.
新入社員の歓迎会を開く。 = しんにゅうしゃいんの かんげいかいを ひらく = shinnyū shain no kangeikai o hiraku = We will hold a welcome party for the new employees.
宴会の招待状 = えんかいのしょうたいじょう = enkai no shōtaijō = banquet invitation, party invitation - General invitation to a banquet or social gathering.
宴会の招待状が届いた。 = えんかいの しょうたいじょうが とどいた = enkai no shōtaijō ga todoita = The banquet invitation arrived.
ご招待 = ごしょうたい = go-shōtai = invitation (polite) - Polite way to refer to an invitation.
ご招待ありがとうございます。 = ごしょうたい ありがとうございます = go-shōtai arigatō gozaimasu = Thank you for the invitation.
招き = まねき = maneki = invitation, beckoning - Being invited or called to an event.
彼の招きで宴会に参加した。 = かれの まねきで えんかいに さんかした = kare no maneki de enkai ni sankashita = I attended the banquet at his invitation.
宴会 = えんかい = enkai = banquet, party, drinking party, social gathering - General term for a party or banquet (often with alcohol).
今週末に宴会がある。 = こんしゅうまつに えんかいが ある = konshūmatsu ni enkai ga aru = There’s a banquet this weekend.
祝宴 = しゅくえん = shukuen = celebratory banquet, feast - Banquet held to celebrate something.
結婚の祝宴を開く。 = けっこんの しゅくえんを ひらく = kekkon no shukuen o hiraku = We will hold a wedding celebratory banquet.
饗宴 = きょうえん = kyōen = grand banquet, feast - Formal and grand banquet.
宮廷で饗宴が催された。 = きゅうていで きょうえんが もよおされた = kyūtei de kyōen ga moyōsareta = A grand banquet was held at the court.
責任 = せきにん = sekinin = responsibility, duty, accountability, liability - Being answerable for one’s actions or duties.
自分の行動に責任を持つ。 = じぶんの こうどうに せきにんを もつ = jibun no kōdō ni sekinin o motsu = Take responsibility for your own actions.
だからこそ = だからこそ = dakara koso = that’s precisely why, for that very reason - Strong emphatic “that’s why”.
彼は努力した。だからこそ成功した。 = かれは どりょくした。だからこそ せいこうした = kare wa doryoku shita. Dakara koso seikō shita = He worked hard. That’s precisely why he succeeded.
落とされた = おとされた = otosareta = was dropped, was made to fall (passive) - Passive form of dropping or losing something.
財布を落とされた。 = さいふを おとされた = saifu o otosareta = I had my wallet dropped / stolen (pickpocketed).
とか = とか = toka = such as, and so on, or something like that, I heard that… - Casual particle for examples or hearsay.
週末は映画見たりとか、友達と遊んだりとかした。 = しゅうまつは えいがみたりとか、ともだちと あそんだりとかした = shūmatsu wa eiga mitari toka, tomodachi to asondari toka shita = On the weekend I watched movies, hung out with friends, and stuff like that.
昨夜 = ゆうべ = yūbe = last night, yesterday evening - Refers to the night of the previous day.
昨夜はよく眠れましたか？ = ゆうべは よく ねむれましたか？ = yūbe wa yoku nemuremashita ka? = Did you sleep well last night?
発光する = はっこうする = hakkō suru = to glow, to luminesce, to emit light - To give off light (especially in the dark).
この塗料は暗闇で発光する。 = このとりょうは くらやみで はっこうする = kono toryō wa kurayami de hakkō suru = This paint glows in the dark.
蓄光性 = ちくこうせい = chikukōsei = photoluminescence, glow-in-the-dark property - The ability of a material to glow after absorbing light.
このおもちゃは蓄光性がある。 = このおもちゃは ちくこうせいが ある = kono omocha wa chikukōsei ga aru = This toy has glow-in-the-dark properties.
暗闇で光る = くらやみでひかる = kurayami de hikaru = to glow/shine in the dark - General phrase for glowing in darkness.
この時計は暗闇で光る。 = このとけいは くらやみで ひかる = kono tokei wa kurayami de hikaru = This watch glows in the dark.
機知に富んだ = きちにとんだ = kichi ni tonda = witty, full of wit, ingenious - Clever and quick-thinking (especially in conversation).
彼は機知に富んだ返事が上手だ。 = かれは きちにとんだ へんじが じょうずだ = kare wa kichi ni tonda henji ga jōzu da = He is good at giving witty replies.




















